-- XOR Decoder - Supports HEX strings and tries all keys

-- Optimized: uses table.concat (no memory explosion)

local hex_string = [[

]]

-- ============================================

-- DECODER - DON'T EDIT BELOW

-- ============================================

local bit_library = bit32 or bit

local encrypted_data = {}

print("=== XOR DECODER - HEX STRING MODE ===")

print()

-- Convert hex string to byte array

if hex_string and hex_string ~= "" then

    print("Converting hex string to bytes...")

    hex_string = hex_string:gsub("%s+", "")

        :gsub("\n", "")

        :gsub("\r", "")

        :gsub("0x", "")

    for i = 1, #hex_string, 2 do

        local hex_byte = hex_string:sub(i, i + 1)

        local byte_val = tonumber(hex_byte, 16)

        if byte_val then

            encrypted_data[#encrypted_data + 1] = byte_val

        end

    end

    print("Converted " .. #encrypted_data .. " bytes from hex")

    print()

else

    print("[ERROR] No hex string found!")

    return

end

-- XOR function

local function xor_bytes(a, b)

    if bit_library and bit_library.bxor then

        return bit_library.bxor(a, b)

    end

    local res, mul = 0, 1

    while a > 0 or b > 0 do

        if (a % 2) ~= (b % 2) then

            res = res + mul

        end

        a = math.floor(a / 2)

        b = math.floor(b / 2)

        mul = mul * 2

    end

    return res

end

-- Optimized decode (NO string concatenation)

local function decode_xor_string(data, key)

    local buffer = table.create and table.create(#data) or {}

    for i = 1, #data do

        buffer[i] = string.char(xor_bytes(data[i], key))

    end

    return table.concat(buffer)

end

-- Save file

local function save_file(content, filename)

    local ok = pcall(function()

        if writefile then

            writefile(filename, content)

        else

            local f = io.open(filename, "w")

            if f then

                f:write(content)

                f:close()

            end

        end

        print("[SAVED] " .. filename)

    end)

    return ok

end

print("Trying all XOR keys (0255)...")

print()

local results = {}

local keywords = {

    "local","function","return","end","if","then",

    "else","for","while","do","and","or","not"

}

for key = 0, 255 do

    if key % 32 == 0 then

        print("Progress:", key .. "/256")

    end

    local result = decode_xor_string(encrypted_data, key)

    local readable = 0

    for i = 1, #result do

        local b = result:byte(i)

        if (b >= 32 and b <= 126) or b == 9 or b == 10 or b == 13 then

            readable = readable + 1

        end

    end

    local lua_score = 0

    for _, kw in ipairs(keywords) do

        local _, c = result:gsub(kw, "")

        lua_score = lua_score + c

    end

    local readability = (readable / #result) * 100

    if readability > 50 or lua_score >= 5 then

        results[#results + 1] = {

            key = key,

            readability = readability,

            lua_score = lua_score,

            content = result

        }

    end

end

print("\n=== DECODING COMPLETE ===\n")

table.sort(results, function(a, b)

    if a.lua_score ~= b.lua_score then

        return a.lua_score > b.lua_score

    end

    return a.readability > b.readability

end)

if #results > 0 then

    print("Found", #results, "possible results\n")

    for i = 1, math.min(5, #results) do

        local r = results[i]

        print(string.format(

            "KEY %d: %.1f%% readable, %d Lua keywords",

            r.key, r.readability, r.lua_score

        ))

        local preview = r.content:sub(1, 150):gsub("\n", " ")

        if #r.content > 150 then preview = preview .. "..." end

        print("Preview:", preview, "\n")

        if i <= 3 then

            save_file(r.content, ("decoded_key_%d.lua"):format(r.key))

        end

    end

else

    print("[WARNING] No readable Lua code found")

end
